{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CY8AnJE7fFDwvdEDmKNQQs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good. Now I understand the setup:\n- ingress-nginx v1.14.1\n- Ingress `otel-echo` routes `otel.example.com` → `otel-echo:5678`\n- The `/otel-check` path is also in the `otel-alt` ingress but that's a decoy\n\nNow I need to patch the `ingress-nginx-controller` ConfigMap with:\n1. `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` - enables OTel\n2. `otlp-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"` - OTel collector host\n3. `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"` - OTel collector port\n4. `otel-sampler: \"AlwaysOn\"` - 100% sampling\n5. `otel-sampler-ratio: \"1.0\"` - explicit ratio\n6. `log-format-upstream` with the required format including `$opentelemetry_trace_id` and `$opentelemetry_span_id`\n\nLet me check the ingress-nginx documentation for v1.14.x to confirm the exact ConfigMap keys for OTel configuration.\n\nFor v1.14.x, I need to set `enable-opentelemetry: \"true\"` along with `otlp-collector-host: \"otel-collector.otel.svc\"` and `otlp-collector-port: \"4317\"`, plus the sampler settings with `otel-sampler-parent-based: \"false\"` to ensure all requests are sampled regardless of parent span context.\n\nNow I'm working on the log format, which needs to include the OpenTelemetry trace and span IDs. The format spans multiple lines in nginx but needs to be represented as a single YAML string in the ConfigMap, so I'll need to handle the line breaks appropriately.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1657,"cache_read_input_tokens":32246,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1657},"output_tokens":37,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8497b89c-d4d0-4d50-b0d3-2bc741363c67","uuid":